          "tz": -240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2013-05-15 15:09:15.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-3270 statahead: avoid freeing minfo with request in flight",
        "message": "LU-3270 statahead: avoid freeing minfo with request in flight\n\nThere is a race in the code where statahead thread would send an\nRPC and then exit without waiting for RPC to complete.\nOn thread exit minfo attached to sai would be freed, but it's also\nreferenced from RPC to be used when RPC reply is received.\nAs such this patch stops freeing minfo from ll_sai_cleanup\nand instead minfo is now freed either in ll_statahead_post after RPC\nis received for normal operations, or in ll_statahead_interpret if we\nreceived a reply after statahead thread terminated.\n\nChange-Id: Ib23af5d3f009a0768d119522382fc863c449f9b4\nSigned-off-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
